# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ZOIKO CHATBOT - LOCAL ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── SMTP Configuration (Custom SMTP - GoDaddy example) ─────────────────────
SMTP_HOST=smtpout.secureserver.net
SMTP_PORT=465
SMTP_USER=support@zoikogroup.com
SMTP_PASS=NoxxMC26070%!LGM

# ── Email Configuration ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SUPPORT_EMAIL=support@zoikomobile.com

# ── Gmail Configuration (Optional - Fallback) ───────────────────────────────
# Set USE_GMAIL=true to use Gmail instead of custom SMTP (more reliable on GCP)
USE_GMAIL=false
GMAIL_USER=your-gmail@gmail.com
GMAIL_PASS=xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# 1. CUSTOM SMTP (GoDaddy)
#    SMTP_HOST: Your GoDaddy SMTP host (usually smtpout.secureserver.net)
#    SMTP_PORT: 465 (SSL) or 587 (TLS)
#    SMTP_USER: Your GoDaddy email (support@zoikogroup.com)
#    SMTP_PASS: Your GoDaddy password
#
# 2. GMAIL (Recommended for GCP)
#    a) Enable 2-Factor Authentication on your Gmail account
#    b) Go to: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
#    c) Generate an app password for "Mail" on "Windows Computer"
#    d) Copy the 16-character password
#    e) Set:
#       USE_GMAIL=true
#       GMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com
#       GMAIL_PASS=<16-char-app-password>

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# TESTING LOCALLY
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# 1. Create .env file from this template:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Fill in your actual values (see above)
#
# 3. Load environment variables:
#    export $(cat .env | xargs)
#
# 4. Run backend:
#    uvicorn backend.app:app --reload
#
# 5. Test health endpoint:
#    curl http://localhost:8000/health
#
# 6. Test email sending:
#    curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/send-request \
#      -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#      -d '{
#        "name": "John Doe",
#        "email": "your-test-email@example.com",
#        "phone": "5551234567",
#        "issue": "Testing email functionality"
#      }'

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# GITHUB SECRETS (FOR GCP DEPLOYMENT)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Copy these secret names to GitHub Settings → Secrets → Actions
# You'll add the same values as in this .env file

# GCP_PROJECT_ID=<your-gcp-project-id>
# GCP_SA_KEY=<json-from-gcp-service-account>
# SMTP_HOST=smtpout.secureserver.net
# SMTP_PORT=465
# SMTP_USER=support@zoikogroup.com
# SMTP_PASS=<your-actual-password>
# SUPPORT_EMAIL=support@zoikomobile.com
# USE_GMAIL=true
# GMAIL_USER=your-gmail@gmail.com
# GMAIL_PASS=<16-char-app-password>

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECURITY NOTES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ⚠️ NEVER commit .env file to Git (add to .gitignore)
# ⚠️ NEVER share passwords in code or emails
